To build on your machine, you will likely need to change the paths below. This requires GSL.

cc -O3 -I/usr/local/include -I /usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/numpy/core/include/ -I /usr/local/include/python2.7/ -L /usr/local/lib -lgsl -lgslcblas lcfit.c -lm -fPIC -shared -o fitlc.so

On cloud or OSG:

cc -fPIC -shared -O3 -I /cvmfs/spt.opensciencegrid.org/py2-v1/RHEL_6_x86_64/i3ports/include/gsl-1.16 -I //cvmfs/spt.opensciencegrid.org/py2-v1/RHEL_6_x86_64/include/python2.7/ lcfit.c -L $SROOT/lib -I /cvmfs/spt.opensciencegrid.org/py2-v1/RHEL_6_x86_64/lib/python2.7/site-packages/numpy/core/include/ -l gsl -l gslcblas  -o fitlc.so

Sam Guns 11-Dec-2018: the following worked for me on scott
cc -fPIC -shared -O3 -I /cvmfs/spt.opensciencegrid.org/py2-v1/RHEL_6_x86_64/include/ -I /cvmfs/spt.opensciencegrid.org/py2-v1/RHEL_6_x86_64/include/python2.7/ tmplfilter.c -L $SROOT/lib -I /cvmfs/spt.opensciencegrid.org/py2-v1/RHEL_6_x86_64/lib/python2.7/site-packages/numpy/core/include/ -l gsl -l gslcblas  -o tmplfilter.so 


